h1. g:joinClasses

h2. Purpose

Joins a list of CSS classes, safely handling null values and ensuring no extra whitespace is produced.

h2. Example

{code:xml}
<div class="${g.joinClasses(values:[userClass, 'notice', 'alert'])}">
..
</div>
{code}

This would output the class attribute as @class="somevalue notice alert"@ if userClass was set to "somevalue".

h2. Attributes

{table}
*Name* | *Purpose* 
values | Required - The list of CSS classes
{table}

